{"id":17529,"date":"2014-01-09T15:05:11","date_gmt":"2014-01-09T11:05:11","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.dailyhadithonline.com\/?p=17529"},"modified":"2024-04-07T11:02:43","modified_gmt":"2024-04-07T07:02:43","slug":"dhikr-virtue-daily","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/01\/09\/dhikr-virtue-daily\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Dhikr: Great virtue of glorifying Allah daily"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<b>Whoever declares one hundred times a day, &#8216;There is no God but Allah without any partner, to Him belongs sovereignty and all praise and He is powerful over everything,&#8217; he will have the reward of emancipating ten slaves, a hundred good deeds will be recorded for him, a hundred sins will be erased from his record, and he will have a guard against Satan during the day until evening. No one will exceed him but one who recited these words more often<\/b>.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 3293, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 2691<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <b><i>Muttafaqun Alayhi\u00a0<\/i><\/b>(authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim<\/p>\n<p align=\"right\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0647\u064f\u0631\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0646\u0651\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0645\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0644\u064e\u0627 \u0625\u0650\u0644\u064e\u0647\u064e \u0625\u0650\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u064f \u0648\u064e\u062d\u0652\u062f\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0644\u064e\u0627 \u